\bI could create a utopia, free of war and crime!

\bHe is the strongest Gym Leader in the region, after all.
\bSorry about this, \pn.\nIt's nothing personal, but the Augur's orders were given.
\bHere are your rewards.\nI am a Gym Leader, after all!
\bI believe in what the Augur is fighting for... but if you don't, you should have a fair chance to stop him.
\bHe's gone to the roof to begin the summoning of Rayquaza.
\bIf you hurry, you should be able to stop him.

\bSorry about this, \pn.\nIt's nothing personal, but the Augur's orders were given.
\bI'd love to change my mind and save you, but I can't.\nI made a promise, and a strong ruler keeps his promises.\nI'm sorry- and farewell.
\bIn my mind's eye, I see a region filled with love.\nIt's a far off, almost unachievable dream.
\bDeath on the way to that goal is a triviality.
\bEast's sacrifice was not in vain, especially now that I can use him to summon Rayquaza.
\bYou can follow me to the roof, if you want.\nTry and stop me, I dare you.\nBut be warned, I'm not going to spare you twice.
\bDid that surprise you? That the Second Augur was on our side all along?
\bDon't underestimate the strength of a legendary Pokemon like Rayquaza.\nThey really are strong.
\bMan, I love East. Definitely the best Leader in the region.
\bThanks for beating East. I never liked the guy.
\bThe Augur... he lied?\nEverything I was taught, everything I grew up believing...\nHow the Augur fought against the cults and was the hero of the nation... that
was a lie?\nI don't know how to feel about this...
\bAll right, \pn! Are you ready?\nWe need to warn the Augur that the Sky Cult is on their way up!\nOtherwise, they might blackmail him into summoning Rayquaza!
